<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/6874915-trudy-brasure"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1442609699i/6874915._UY100_CR7,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/6874915-trudy-brasure">Trudy Brasure</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Mr. Thornton performs a hell of a lot of self-sacrifice as well. Why doesn&apos;t he also grow a spine? I&apos;m acting as devil&apos;s advocate here to some degree,<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Mr. Thornton performs a hell of a lot of self-sacrifice as well. Why doesn't he also grow a spine? I'm acting as devil's advocate here to some degree, but I'm curious how working oneself to the bone for the sake of others can be interpreted as self-righteous and wimpy. Thornton and Margaret are a lot alike: they both struggle to support their families.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
