<div id="review_3536722494" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3536722494" />
    <a title="Mara" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/70492479-mara"><img alt="Mara" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1572141381p2/70492479.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3536722494?book_show_action=true">Sep 07, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mara" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mara" href="/user/show/70492479-mara">Mara</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/70492479-mara?shelf=physical-owned">physical-owned</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3536722494" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4835587348632126627">It&apos;s always hard for me to review well known classics, because, really, what is there to say about a book that has stood the test of time for such self-evident reasons. The prose- wonderful. The characters- beautifully developed. The themes- resonant (and I particularly enjoyed Mr. Hale&apos;s conflict of conscious, though I know most people think of this as a great novel about class and rising/falling fortunes). The plot was probably the bit I liked least, but still, nothing really to complain about</span>
  <span id="freeText4835587348632126627" style="display:none">It's always hard for me to review well known classics, because, really, what is there to say about a book that has stood the test of time for such self-evident reasons. The prose- wonderful. The characters- beautifully developed. The themes- resonant (and I particularly enjoyed Mr. Hale's conflict of conscious, though I know most people think of this as a great novel about class and rising/falling fortunes). The plot was probably the bit I liked least, but still, nothing really to complain about, just a bit unevely paced for my tastes. This is the kind of book I think I will grow enjoy more with rereading, so I wouldn't be surprised if I end up thinking of this as a favorite</span>
  <a data-text-id="4835587348632126627" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

